Subject: [PATCH] stdlib/public/Cxx/std: forward the libc++ wchar.h
 const-overloads guard through -Xcc for the CxxStdlib stdlib build itself

NDK 30's libc++ module map marks C compatibility headers such as
<wchar.h> as textual. While importing the Android libc++ std module here,
Clang can textually include libc++'s <wchar.h> more than once and hit
duplicate definitions for its preferred-overload shims (wcschr, wcspbrk,
wcsrchr, wcsstr, wmemchr). patches/swift/0001-clangimporter-libcxx-cxxstdlib.patch
already fixes this at the ClangImporter level (defining
_LIBCPP_WCHAR_H_HAS_CONST_OVERLOADS=1 for every Android ClangImporter
invocation), which covers everything downstream of a rebuilt host
toolchain. This patch forwards the same guard via -Xcc for the CxxStdlib
stdlib build's own compile line, so a source tree can still build (or
rebuild) swiftCxxStdlib for Android against a not-yet-rebuilt host swiftc.
Inert on non-Android SDKs.

This patch is a candidate for filing upstream.

Sentinel: NUCLEUS_SWIFT_SOURCE_ANDROID_CXXSTDLIB_WCHAR_WORKAROUND

diff --git a/stdlib/public/Cxx/std/CMakeLists.txt b/stdlib/public/Cxx/std/CMakeLists.txt
index 0165f9aff50..5ce584bf526 100644
--- a/stdlib/public/Cxx/std/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/stdlib/public/Cxx/std/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -43,6 +43,17 @@ add_swift_target_library(swiftCxxStdlib STATIC NO_LINK_NAME IS_STDLIB IS_SWIFT_O

     SWIFT_COMPILE_FLAGS ${SWIFT_RUNTIME_SWIFT_COMPILE_FLAGS} ${SWIFT_STANDARD_LIBRARY_SWIFT_FLAGS}
     -cxx-interoperability-mode=default
+    # NDK 30's libc++ module map marks C compatibility headers such as
+    # <wchar.h> as textual. While importing the Android libc++ std module
+    # here, Clang can textually include libc++'s <wchar.h> more than once
+    # and hit duplicate definitions for its preferred-overload shims
+    # (wcschr, wcspbrk, wcsrchr, wcsstr, wmemchr). Forward libc++'s own
+    # guard for that redundant shim block through to the ClangImporter's
+    # invocation via -Xcc; inert on non-Android SDKs (swift-toolchain
+    # carries the equivalent fix as a compiler source patch, but that
+    # requires rebuilding the host toolchain — this achieves the same
+    # effect for stdlib-build-time compiles without one).
+    -Xcc -D_LIBCPP_WCHAR_H_HAS_CONST_OVERLOADS=1
     -Xfrontend -module-interface-preserve-types-as-written
     -Xfrontend -disable-module-selectors-in-module-interface

